    "title": {
      "rendered": "8 Fundraising Tools to Watch in 2017"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><strong><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/8-Fundraising-Tools-to-Watch-2017.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-20915\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/8-Fundraising-Tools-to-Watch-2017-300x292.jpg?resize=300%2C292\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"292\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/8-Fundraising-Tools-to-Watch-2017.jpg?resize=300%2C292&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/8-Fundraising-Tools-to-Watch-2017.jpg?resize=768%2C747&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/8-Fundraising-Tools-to-Watch-2017.jpg?w=800&amp;ssl=1 800w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2016/12/22/5-digital-payment-systems-that-could-transform-online-fundraising/\">Digital payments</a> </strong>are going to make a big impact on social and mobile media\u00a0in 2017, but there are some new fundraising services and niche tools and apps that speak to current fundraising trends in the nonprofit sector i.e., the decreased of use cash, the rapid rise of the app economy, and gaming for good. That said, launching a fundraising start-up is not easy and the odds of making it long-term are slim. Your experimentation with at least one of the tools below (or from the\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2016/01/25/8-fundraising-tools-to-watch-in-2016/\"><strong>2016 list</strong></a> and <strong><a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2015/04/11/9-fundraising-tools-to-watch-in-2015/\">2015 list</a></strong>), would be greatly appreciated by their founders.</p>\n<hr />\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">1) Brackets for Good<br />\n<a href=\"https://bfg.org/\" target=\"_blank\">bfg.org</a></h1>\n<p><em>Brackets for Good</em> hosts online, bracket-style fundraising tournaments that encourage donors to out-fundraise their opponents on behalf of their favorite nonprofit. The winner of the tournament receives a $100,000 grand prize.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://bfg.org/\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20905\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Branckets-for-Good.jpg?resize=600%2C435\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"435\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Branckets-for-Good.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Branckets-for-Good.jpg?resize=300%2C218&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">2) Bstow<br />\n<a href=\"https://bstow.com/\" target=\"_blank\">bstow.com</a></h1>\n<p><em>Bstow</em> is a mobile app that allows users to easily roundup credit and debit purchases to be automatically donated to their favorite nonprofits. Users can set a monthly limit and donate to any nonprofit in the United States.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://bstow.com/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20923\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/bstow.jpg?resize=600%2C365\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"365\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/bstow.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/bstow.jpg?resize=300%2C183&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">3) Dipjar<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.dipjar.com/\" target=\"_blank\">dipjar.com</a></h1>\n<p><em>DipJar</em> enables cashless donations via tip jars and donation boxes for credit cards. The service manages every aspect of transactions, from processing to payout.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.dipjar.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-20809 size-full\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dipjar-1.png?resize=600%2C280\" width=\"600\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dipjar-1.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Dipjar-1.png?resize=300%2C140&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">\u00a04) Goodpin<br />\n<a class=\"u-textUserColor\" title=\"http://www.good.pn\" href=\"https://www.good.pn\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"me nofollow noopener\">good.pn</a></h1>\n<p><em>Goodpin (currently in beta)</em> is a hub of special offers\u00a0on products and services offered by brands that can be redeemed by making a donation to participating nonprofits.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.good.pn\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20912\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Goodpin.png?resize=600%2C273\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"273\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Goodpin.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Goodpin.png?resize=300%2C137&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">5) Goodworld<br />\n<a href=\"https://goodworld.me\" target=\"_blank\">goodworld.me</a></h1>\n<p><em>Goodworld</em> enables donors to give on Facebook and Twitter with two taps and a\u00a0#donate hashtag. Recently relaunched with an improved design and donation process, the service now also offers <strong><a href=\"https://goodworld.me/60/beagle-freedom-project\" target=\"_blank\">two-tap giving on the web</a></strong>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://goodworld.me\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20951\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Goodworld.png?resize=600%2C276\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"276\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Goodworld.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Goodworld.png?resize=300%2C138&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">6) Internet of Things (IoT) Buttons<br />\n<a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/iotbutton/\" target=\"_blank\">amazon.com/iotbutton</a></h1>\n<p><em>The AWS IoT Button</em> is a programmable button based on the <strong><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Dash-Buttons/b?ie=UTF8&amp;node=10667898011\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon Dash Button</a></strong> hardware. In addition to these<strong> <a href=\"http://www.dashbuttondudes.com/blog/2015/12/11/26-amazon-dash-button-hacks\" target=\"_blank\">26 interesting hacks of the AWS Iot button</a></strong>,\u00a0one coder has created an <a href=\"http://gizmodo.com/how-to-make-an-amazon-dash-button-that-gives-the-aclu-1792091727\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Amazon Dash button that\u00a0donates to the ACLU</strong></a>. In\u00a02017 it will be interesting to watch if the nonprofit sector adopts the technology and creates more IoT Buttons for donating and advocacy. That said, there is one problem with the Amazon Dash Button: t<em>he battery is not replaceable or rechargeable</em>, so the hardware does need to be more sustainable for it to be widely adopted by the social good sector. Perhaps a new button hardware will be introduced by a service other than Amazon?</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/iotbutton/\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20944\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/iot-button.png?resize=600%2C272\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"272\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/iot-button.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/iot-button.png?resize=300%2C136&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">7) Spotfund<br />\n<a href=\"http://spotfund.com/\" target=\"_blank\">spotfund.com</a></h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>Spotfund</em> is a location-based mobile app that allows users to search for stories (created by nonprofits) to donate to that are in near proximity or located in their local community.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.spotfund.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20927\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Spotfund.png?resize=600%2C287\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"287\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Spotfund.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Spotfund.png?resize=300%2C144&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">8) Tiltify<br />\n<a href=\"https://tiltify.com\" target=\"_blank\">tiltify.com</a></h1>\n<p><em>Tiltify</em> is a crowdfunding service\u00a0for gamers that enables them to raise money through online streams\u00a0like <strong><a href=\"https://www.twitch.tv/\" target=\"_blank\">Twitch.tv</a></strong> and YouTube. Gamers can use the service to recruit online donations, create rewards, track progress, and create fundraising teams.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://tiltify.com\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20919\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Tilitify.png?resize=600%2C349\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"349\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Tilitify.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Tilitify.png?resize=300%2C175&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Based upon the survey results of 4,908 NGOs worldwide, the <strong><a href=\"http://techreport.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\">2017 Global NGO Online Technology Report</a></strong> is groundbreaking in that it is the only annual research project dedicated to studying how NGOs use online technology on a global scale.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://techreport.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20878\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Tech-Report-Promo-1-English-Nonprofit-Tech-for-Good.jpg?resize=600%2C315\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"315\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Tech-Report-Promo-1-English-Nonprofit-Tech-for-Good.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Tech-Report-Promo-1-English-Nonprofit-Tech-for-Good.jpg?resize=300%2C158&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n",
